com.password4j

Class SecureString

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.password4j.SecureString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CharSequence

    public class SecureString
extends Object
implements CharSequence
    More secure implementation of a String, preventing heap memory attacks. Like String, this CharSequence implementation has an underlying array of chars. The sequence however is not stored in the String pool and the array of chars lives temporary in the heap memory.
    Since:
    1.2.0
    Author:
    David Bertoldi

      • SecureString

        public SecureString(char[] chars,
                    boolean eraseSource)
        Creates a SecureString from an array of chars. Important: if the second argument is true, the original array is zeroed after the object creation! Each char is replaced with Character.MIN_VALUE

        The sequence is never put in the String pool.

        Parameters:
        chars - sequence of characters
        eraseSource - if true, the original array is zeroed
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if null is passed
        Since:
        1.2.0
